Invoking: `validate` with `{'patch': "--- a/ext/spl/spl_dllist.c\n+++ b/ext/spl/spl_dllist.c\n@@ -1023,10 +1023,13 @@\n \twhile (current) {\n-\t\tsmart_str_appendc(&buf, ':');\n-\t\tnext = current->next;\n-\n-\t\tphp_var_serialize(&buf, &current->data, &var_hash);\n-\n-\t\tcurrent = next;\n+\t\tsmart_str_appendc(&buf, ':');\n+\t\t/* Save next pointer before serialization in case current is freed during serialization */\n+\t\tnext = current->next;\n+\t\tphp_var_serialize(&buf, &current->data, &var_hash);\n+\t\tcurrent = next;\n \t}\n"}`
responded: The previous patch did not resolve the use-after-free because the bug is not just about skipping undefined data, but about the fact that the linked list structure itself can be modified (and elements freed) during serialization, possibly due to user code (e.g., via custom object handlers or destructors triggered by serialization). This means that after `php_var_serialize(&buf, &current->data, &var_hash);`, the `current` pointer (and/or its `next` pointer) may be dangling.

**Correct approach:**  
- Save `current->next` **before** calling `php_var_serialize`, so that even if `current` is freed during serialization, we do not dereference it after that point.

Here is the correct patch:

```diff
--- a/ext/spl/spl_dllist.c
+++ b/ext/spl/spl_dllist.c
@@ -1023,10 +1023,13 @@
 	while (current) {
-		smart_str_appendc(&buf, ':');
-		next = current->next;
-
-		php_var_serialize(&buf, &current->data, &var_hash);
-
-		current = next;
+		smart_str_appendc(&buf, ':');
+		/* Save next pointer before serialization in case current is freed during serialization */
+		next = current->next;
+		php_var_serialize(&buf, &current->data, &var_hash);
+		current = next;
 	}
```

This ensures we never dereference a potentially freed `current` after serialization. Now, let's validate this patch.

args.patch:
diff --git a/ext/spl/spl_dllist.c b/ext/spl/spl_dllist.c
index 6592efc4e5e..0f0f9150ce3 100644
--- a/ext/spl/spl_dllist.c
+++ b/ext/spl/spl_dllist.c
@@ -1022,10 +1022,9 @@ PHP_METHOD(SplDoublyLinkedList, serialize)
 	/* elements */
 	while (current) {
 		smart_str_appendc(&buf, ':');
+		/* Save next pointer before serialization in case current is freed during serialization */
 		next = current->next;
-
 		php_var_serialize(&buf, &current->data, &var_hash);
-
 		current = next;
 	}

